-- Euro Little Changed as Draghi Sees ‘Gradual’ Recovery in 2013
-- B y   N e a l   A r m s t r o n g
-- 2012-12-06T13:38:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-06/euro-little-changed-as-draghi-sees-gradual-recovery-in-2013.html
The euro stayed little changed as
European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi  said the region’s
economy should gradually recover next year.  The 17-nation currency traded at $1.3076 and 107.70 yen at
1:36 p.m. London time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
